for a little while?

87
00:06:42,861 --> 00:06:44,901
‐ Oh great, that’s perfect.

88
00:06:45,030 --> 00:06:46,030
This will be so fun.

89
00:06:47,198 --> 00:06:48,908
‐ Just pretend that
this is your house

90
00:06:49,034 --> 00:06:51,374
and then do whatever
you want to do

91
00:06:51,453 --> 00:06:54,293
and then I’ll do the
same as well, okay.

92
00:06:54,414 --> 00:06:58,254
Well, I will stay within
certain boundaries.

93
00:06:58,335 --> 00:06:59,925
‐ [Woman] Haruko, you
have another friend here

94
00:07:00,045 --> 00:07:01,095
to visit you.

95
00:07:01,171 --> 00:07:02,631
I’m sending her in.

96
00:07:02,756 --> 00:07:03,586
‐ Okay.

97
00:07:06,760 --> 00:07:07,890
‐ Wow.

98
00:07:07,969 --> 00:07:10,099
Now there are three
little sisters.

99
00:07:10,221 --> 00:07:12,471
‐ Oh its alright, Karen,
don’t worry about him.

100
00:07:12,599 --> 00:07:14,559
My big brother won’t
act on what he says.

101
00:07:15,727 --> 00:07:18,097
‐ Hey, you brought me
a change of clothes.

102
00:07:18,229 --> 00:07:19,059
Thanks a lot.

103
00:07:20,148 --> 00:07:21,438
‐ You’re welcome.

104
00:07:21,524 --> 00:07:24,824
Ms. Miina, can we go
somewhere and talk for awhile?

105
00:07:26,237 --> 00:07:27,067
‐ Sure, Karen.

106
00:07:30,784 --> 00:07:32,624
Why did we come
to a public bath?

107
00:07:33,787 --> 00:07:35,617
‐ You know what they
say, naked people

108
00:07:35,705 --> 00:07:37,115
bear their hearts right?

109
00:07:37,207 --> 00:07:39,377
Besides, whenever I’ve
had a really important

110
00:07:39,459 --> 00:07:41,839
conversation with you,
it’s almost always

111
00:07:41,962 --> 00:07:43,092
been in the bathtub.

112
00:07:44,506 --> 00:07:46,336
‐ It was like our own
secret room where Mike

113
00:07:46,466 --> 00:07:48,046
couldn’t hear what
we were saying.

114
00:07:48,134 --> 00:07:49,094
‐ Yeah.

115
00:07:50,303 --> 00:07:51,473
‐ So you seem like
you’re doing okay.

116
00:07:51,554 --> 00:07:53,564
I thought you’d be
depressed because

117
00:07:53,640 --> 00:07:56,060
of what’s been happening
over the last few days.

118
00:07:56,142 --> 00:07:57,982
‐ I am depressed, Ms. Miina.

119
00:07:58,061 --> 00:08:01,311
But there’s a part of me that’s
really happy I found out.

120
00:08:01,439 --> 00:08:04,069
That I’m the one
related to Mr. Mike.

121
00:08:04,150 --> 00:08:05,650
‐ Yeah.

122
00:08:05,777 --> 00:08:09,317
‐ And then last night when
you left the house, Ms. Miina,

123
00:08:09,447 --> 00:08:10,947
I realized something.

124
00:08:11,032 --> 00:08:13,332
I love Mr. Mike like
a little sister should

125
00:08:13,451 --> 00:08:15,831
and I really love
having you as my friend

126
00:08:15,912 --> 00:08:17,962
and I love the three of us.

127
00:08:18,832 --> 00:08:20,372
I love us all together.

128
00:08:21,835 --> 00:08:22,675
‐ Karen.

129
00:08:23,837 --> 00:08:25,247
‐ I want the three
of us together.

130
00:08:25,338 --> 00:08:28,798
I want us all together
living in that house.

131
00:08:30,260 --> 00:08:31,260
‐ Thank you.

132
00:08:33,555 --> 00:08:35,015
‐ Would you mind telling me?

133
00:08:35,140 --> 00:08:37,350
What made you decide
to leave the house?

134
00:08:38,852 --> 00:08:40,852
‐ I left because I’m a stranger.

135
00:08:40,979 --> 00:08:42,309
Its not my home.

136
00:08:42,397 --> 00:08:44,357
‐ If you really meant that,
you wouldn’t of chosen

137
00:08:44,482 --> 00:08:45,902
Haruko’s house to run to.

138
00:08:46,026 --> 00:08:48,896
I think you would of
gone much farther away.

139
00:08:49,029 --> 00:08:50,859
You have another
reason, don’t you?

140
00:08:50,989 --> 00:08:52,409
‐ Well I.

141
00:08:52,532 --> 00:08:54,872
‐ You know that you
can stay in the house

142
00:08:54,951 --> 00:08:57,751
and you can stay in love
with Mr. Mike if you want.

143
00:08:57,871 --> 00:09:00,121
You can even tell him
you’re in love with him.

144
00:09:00,206 --> 00:09:02,376
Right now, Ms. Miina,
you’re not even talking

145
00:09:02,500 --> 00:09:03,290
to Mr. Mike.

146
00:09:05,545 --> 00:09:08,965
Oh my, that’s not
because of me, is it?

147
00:09:09,049 --> 00:09:10,509
‐ Its not that.

148
00:09:10,592 --> 00:09:13,392
Well, part of me may think that.

149
00:09:13,470 --> 00:09:15,510
But that’s really
not the reason.

150
00:09:15,597 --> 00:09:18,557
‐ But Ms. Miina, love
alliance rule number three

151
00:09:18,641 --> 00:09:20,561
is still fully active.

152
00:09:20,643 --> 00:09:23,853
Whoever ends up being
related to Mr. Mike

153
00:09:23,938 --> 00:09:26,268
must support the others
romance with him.

154
00:09:27,317 --> 00:09:28,147
‐ But, Karen.

155
00:09:29,569 --> 00:09:32,449
‐ I wouldn’t want anyone else
to be Mr. Mike’s girlfriend

156
00:09:32,572 --> 00:09:33,412
but you.

157
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:36,700
You’re the one for my brother.

158
00:09:39,079 --> 00:09:41,909
‐ Thanks Karen, I appreciate it.

159
00:09:41,998 --> 00:09:44,288
But can you hold off on
the idea of me going back

160
00:09:44,417 --> 00:09:46,087
to the house for a bit?

161
00:09:46,211 --> 00:09:47,591
‐ Why do you want that?

162
00:09:47,712 --> 00:09:49,012
‐ Well because.

163
00:09:49,089 --> 00:09:52,799
‐ Please tell me.

164
00:09:52,926 --> 00:09:54,426
Ms. Miina?

165
00:09:54,552 --> 00:09:55,932
‐ I can’t look.

166
00:09:56,054 --> 00:09:56,934
‐ What?

167
00:09:57,013 --> 00:09:58,393
‐ I can’t look at him.

168
00:09:58,473 --> 00:10:01,063
Ever since I found out that
Mike wasn’t my brother,

169
00:10:01,142 --> 00:10:03,392
I haven’t been able to
look him in the face.

170
00:10:03,478 --> 00:10:05,608
Its strange but I can’t.

171
00:10:05,688 --> 00:10:09,028
My heart just starts to
race when he talks to me.

172
00:10:09,109 --> 00:10:10,779
I can’t believe I’m
feeling this way.

173
00:10:10,902 --> 00:10:14,322
I just, I just can’t see
anyone other than mike

174
00:10:14,447 --> 00:10:17,617
but if we, if I.

175
00:10:20,537 --> 00:10:21,537
‐ Ms. Miina.

176
00:10:25,375 --> 00:10:26,755
‐ Both of them are so innocent.

177
00:10:26,835 --> 00:10:27,885
Its so cute.

178
00:10:27,961 --> 00:10:29,001
‐ Yeah it is.

179
00:10:29,129 --> 00:10:31,089
‐ Its so nice to be young.

180
00:10:31,172 --> 00:10:32,132
(laughing)

181
00:10:32,257 --> 00:10:34,337
‐ You sound like an old woman.

182
00:10:34,467 --> 00:10:35,337
‐ You.

183
00:10:35,468 --> 00:10:37,598
I’ll do something dreadful.

184
00:10:37,679 --> 00:10:39,219
(screaming)

185
00:10:39,305 --> 00:10:40,255
‐ [Haruko] I’m sorry.

186
00:10:40,348 --> 00:10:41,268
Somebody help me.

187
00:10:41,349 --> 00:10:43,309
I’m in trouble.

188
00:10:43,434 --> 00:10:44,564
Stop it.

189
00:10:44,644 --> 00:10:47,104
‐ Tsubaki, I’m so
lonely here without you.

190
00:10:51,776 --> 00:10:53,186
Who is that?

191
00:10:54,863 --> 00:10:57,073
‐ [Mike] So it didn’t
work out with Miina, huh?

192
00:10:57,157 --> 00:10:59,487
‐ [Karen] I’m sorry, but
she said she’d come back

193
00:10:59,576 --> 00:11:01,986
so she’s not gone forever.

194
00:11:02,120 --> 00:11:03,660
‐ Well, its’ alright.

195
00:11:03,746 --> 00:11:05,826
As long as we know where she is.

196
00:11:05,915 --> 00:11:06,705
We’ll be fine.

197
00:11:07,876 --> 00:11:09,626
To think that ruined
house had records in it

198
00:11:09,711 --> 00:11:12,251
that answered questions
about our past.

199
00:11:12,338 --> 00:11:13,588
You know, Karen, the weird thing

200
00:11:13,673 --> 00:11:15,263
its so run down it
doesn’t look like anyone’s

201
00:11:15,341 --> 00:11:17,341
been living there for
at least 20 years.

202
00:11:18,553 --> 00:11:20,183
‐ There’s no way.

203
00:11:20,263 --> 00:11:22,853
According to the information
in our mother’s notebook,

204
00:11:22,974 --> 00:11:24,564
the house that the
three of us lived in for

205
00:11:24,684 --> 00:11:27,524
the first couple years of
our lives was this one.

206
00:11:27,604 --> 00:11:29,984
So this really is our house.

207
00:11:30,064 --> 00:11:30,904
‐ Yeah.

208
00:11:31,024 --> 00:11:31,984
Guess you’re right.

209
00:11:33,151 --> 00:11:35,531
You know even after we
read that entire diary,

210
00:11:35,612 --> 00:11:38,532
we still have no real
idea of who our mother is

211
00:11:38,656 --> 00:11:42,196
but the diary should serve
us some sort of clue.

212
00:11:42,285 --> 00:11:45,085
So if you want me to, I
can begin a full search

213
00:11:45,205 --> 00:11:46,085
for our mother.

214
00:11:47,498 --> 00:11:50,078
‐ I don’t know, Mr. Mike, what
do you think we should do?

215
00:11:50,210 --> 00:11:52,590
‐ I think we
shouldn’t do anything.

216
00:11:53,796 --> 00:11:56,336
‐ You’re right,
I agree with you.

217
00:11:56,424 --> 00:11:57,764
‐ So it doesn’t bother you?

218
00:11:59,552 --> 00:12:01,932
‐ I’d be lying if I said
it didn’t bother me at all.

219
00:12:02,055 --> 00:12:05,685
But I think that you
said it best, Mr. Mike.

220
00:12:05,767 --> 00:12:08,937
All that really
matters is now, right?

221
00:12:09,062 --> 00:12:10,732
You and I, in that house.

222
00:12:10,813 --> 00:12:13,273
Miina, you and I in that house,

223
00:12:13,399 --> 00:12:16,239
the three of us living
together as a family,

224
00:12:17,153 --> 00:12:18,993
that would be my perfect now.

225
00:12:20,114 --> 00:12:22,164
‐ But that’s not
the case for Miina.

226
00:12:22,242 --> 00:12:23,492
‐ But Mr. Mike.

227
00:12:23,576 --> 00:12:24,866
‐ Isn’t that right?

228
00:12:24,953 --> 00:12:27,713
As soon as she found out
that she wasn’t related

229
00:12:27,789 --> 00:12:30,539
she put a lot of distance
between her and us.

230
00:12:30,625 --> 00:12:32,755
I don’t care if she’s a
relative or a stranger

231
00:12:32,835 --> 00:12:35,495
but I guess it must
be important to her.

232
00:12:35,588 --> 00:12:37,378
‐ No that’s not it.

233
00:12:37,465 --> 00:12:39,005
I promise you that Ms.
Miina isn’t worried

234
00:12:39,092 --> 00:12:41,012
about any of that at the moment.

235
00:12:41,094 --> 00:12:43,264
She’s looking at
what’s happening now.

236
00:12:43,346 --> 00:12:45,596
I can tell, I’m sure of it.

237
00:12:45,682 --> 00:12:48,392
‐ Alright then, what
is now for Miina?

238
00:12:50,603 --> 00:12:53,523
‐ That’s really not for
me to say, I’m sorry.

239
00:12:53,606 --> 00:12:56,476
But please don’t stop
believing in her.

240
00:12:56,609 --> 00:12:59,449
Right now, Ms. Miina is.

