00:13:02,615 --> 00:13:04,235
but it really
hasn’t sunk in yet.

243
00:13:05,451 --> 00:13:07,751
From my standpoint, you
and Miina act a lot more

244
00:13:07,829 --> 00:13:09,619
like your twins
then we ever have.

245
00:13:10,832 --> 00:13:12,252
‐ But we are twins.

246
00:13:12,333 --> 00:13:13,293
‐ Oh?

247
00:13:13,418 --> 00:13:14,998
‐ Even though we’re not related.

248
00:13:15,128 --> 00:13:17,298
She and I are
still twin sisters.

249
00:13:20,300 --> 00:13:21,130
‐ Karen!

250
00:13:22,593 --> 00:13:24,303
‐ Haruko, what’s wrong?

251
00:13:24,387 --> 00:13:25,717
‐ Karen.

252
00:13:25,805 --> 00:13:27,595
Mii, Mii, it’s Miina.

253
00:13:28,891 --> 00:13:30,181
‐ What’s wrong with Miina?

254
00:13:31,769 --> 00:13:33,059
(soft instrumental music)

255
00:13:33,146 --> 00:13:35,476
‐ Miina said she
was leaving town.

256
00:13:35,606 --> 00:13:36,856
I tried to talk her out of it

